## 🏷️ 4. DHCP — Automated IP Assignment

### The DORA Process

| Step | Message | Direction | Port |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **D**iscover | Client broadcasts (255.255.255.255) | UDP 67 |
| 2 | **O**ffer | Server offers IP/mask/gateway/DNS/lease time to client MAC | UDP 68 |
| 3 | **R**equest | Client broadcasts acceptance of chosen offer | UDP 67 |
| 4 | **A**cknowledge | Server confirms lease (DHCPACK), marks IP in-use | UDP 68 |

### Leases
- IPs are **leased**, not permanent
- Client attempts renewal ~halfway through lease
- If renewal fails, retries closer to expiry
- Unrenewed lease → IP returns to pool, reassignable

