## ⚠️ Common Mistakes & Troubleshooting

### DNS
| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| Typo in domain | Double-check spelling; test with `ping`/`nslookup`/`dig` |
| Wrong DNS server config | Check via `ipconfig /all` or `cat /etc/resolv.conf`; try `nslookup www.google.com 8.8.8.8` to bypass local DNS |
| Firewall blocking UDP 53 | Check local/network firewall rules |

### DHCP
| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| Static IP conflicts with DHCP-assigned IP | Keep static IPs outside the DHCP pool range |
| DHCP server unreachable | Check router status/restart; confirm client is on correct network segment |

### ARP
| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| Stale/incorrect ARP cache | Clear it: `arp -d *` (Windows) or `sudo ip neigh flush all` (Linux/macOS) |
| Suspected ARP spoofing | Check `arp -a` for unexpected MAC on a known IP; use NIDS for detection |

### HTTPS
| Error | Meaning/Fix |
|---|---|
| `NET::ERR_CERT_AUTHORITY_INVALID` | Check system clock sync; cert may genuinely be invalid/expired |
| `NET::ERR_SSL_PROTOCOL_ERROR` / cipher mismatch | TLS version/cipher incompatibility, often an old client or server |

