## 🛡️ Defensive Engineering

### HTTP/HTTPS
- Enforce **HSTS** to force HTTPS-only connections
- Use strong cipher suites; disable SSLv3/TLS 1.0/1.1
- **Input validation** on all POST/GET data (prevent SQLi, XSS)
- **CSP** headers to restrict what resources can load
- **Rate limiting** on login/API endpoints

### DNS
- Deploy **DNSSEC** on authoritative servers
- Use trusted recursive resolvers (Cloudflare, Google, or hardened internal)
- DNS firewalling/filtering against known-malicious domains
- Monitor DNS logs for anomalies (spikes in NXDOMAIN, suspicious query patterns)
- Use **DoH/DoT** to encrypt DNS queries in transit

### DHCP
- **DHCP snooping** on managed switches — validates legit vs malicious DHCP server messages, builds IP-MAC binding table
- Static IPs for critical infrastructure (servers, routers, firewalls)
- Harden the DHCP server itself
- Defend against **DHCP starvation attacks** (pool exhaustion) via snooping + rate limiting

### ARP
- **Static ARP entries** for critical devices (manual, not scalable)
- **Dynamic ARP Inspection (DAI)** on managed switches — validates ARP against DHCP snooping binding table
- Network segmentation (VLANs) to limit spoofing blast radius
- NIDS to detect ARP spoofing patterns

