## 📝 Chapter Summary

- **HTTP** — request/response backbone of the web; methods, status codes, headers, version evolution (1.0 → 1.1 → 2 → 3/QUIC)
- **HTTPS** — HTTP + TLS/SSL for encryption, authentication, integrity via the TLS handshake and CA-issued certificates
- **DNS** — hierarchical name resolution (root → TLD → authoritative), various record types, DNSSEC for integrity
- **DHCP** — automated IP assignment via DORA, leased not permanent
- **ARP** — resolves IP → MAC on the local network, enabling Ethernet frame delivery
- All five protocols interlock in a single page-load: DHCP gets you online, DNS finds the destination, ARP gets the packet to your gateway, HTTP(S) carries the actual content

